General.Name: Odin Metals Ltd
General.Description: Odin Metals Limited engages in mineral exploration activities in Australia. The company primarily explores for copper and base metals deposits. It owns an interest in the Koonenberry project that includes 5 exploration licenses covering an area of 2600 square kilometers located in New South Wales. The company was formerly known as Lawson Gold Limited and changed its name to Odin Metals Limited in October 2017. Odin Metals Limited was incorporated in 2010 and is based in Melbourne, Australia.
